div.p:
Having read in ſome Papers of your zeal in promoting the Goſpel of Chriſt; it is good to be zealouſly affected alwayes in a good matter: But O ye Rulers, ſee you to your matter,2 Sam. 15.3. for there is a way that ſeems right to a man, but the end thereof is death; and there may be a zeal, but not according to knowledge. And there is a name to things,
                  Rom. 10.2. Rev. 2.9. Gal. 1.9. but the things are not ſo as they are named. And there may be that called Goſpel, and preached for it, and it not the Goſpel of our Lord Jeſus Chriſt. Now let them be accurſed that preaches it; but be you free, and be not partakers of other mens ſins, that both you and the Nations may be freed from the plagues of Babylon; for if you ſupport her not, ſhe cannot ſtand;
                  Rev. 18.4. but if you ſupport her, you muſt perſecute▪ and that will be grievous for you one day, who have been ſuch great Profeſſors, and by whom the Lord hath removed perſecutors that was before you.
